<TD><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>Columnist Calls Roamer
Administration Fee One&nbsp;</FONT></FONT></B>
<BR><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica"><FONT SIZE=+1>of "Technology's Hidden
Costs"</FONT></FONT></B></TD>

<TD></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD></TD>

<TD><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">A $3.50 roaming fee is charged on a monthly
basis anytime a phone is used outside the home service area, the columnist
writes.&nbsp; Other cell-phone companies can charge a similar fee every
day you use your phone in their area. It gets passed on through your company.
And, like other roaming fees, it gets assessed on incoming, as well as
outgoing, calls. (<A HREF="http://www.usatoday.com/life/cyber/tech/ctd357.htm">USA
TODAY</A>)</FONT></TD>

